Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.73,0:32:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As you read this I realize exactly what it difer크
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.59,0:32:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so there's two levels of truth, isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.05,0:33:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.97,0:33:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, there's all kinds of critical stuff about acupuncture.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.10,0:33:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose it's still out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.30,0:33:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably, I hate acupuncture websites, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.96,0:33:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Poo-pooing the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.42,0:33:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it was my ulcer, and I'll tell you, I eat anything and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.05,0:33:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what I'm trying to do is redefine what is reality, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.42,0:33:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is more than a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.31,0:33:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more than a dictum.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.68,0:33:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more than a belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.27,0:33:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's subjectively experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.07,0:33:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Subjectively experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.55,0:33:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So the things we write about, then, in our lectures and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.79,0:33:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with verifiably experiential, subjectively experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.74,0:33:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, as Descartes said, res interna versus res externa.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.23,0:34:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Res interna has to do with res cogitans, cognitans.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.28,0:34:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with what you think, opinion and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.53,0:34:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's res externa, which is the world the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.34,0:34:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And the disparity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.73,0:34:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Man can't tell the difference between his thoughts and views and opinions
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.73,0:34:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.17,0:34:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see the academic intellect says acupuncture is unscientific and doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.07,0:34:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's res interna, which tends to be considerably progressively more and more
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.69,0:34:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,just egotistical.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.21,0:34:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, because a critic of acupuncture, I should say to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.82,0:34:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, have you ever tried it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.17,0:34:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.28,0:34:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.63,0:34:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So the experiential, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.11,0:34:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've created a clinical science, experiential, subjectively verifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.19,0:34:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And as consciousness evolves, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.38,0:35:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it represents itself as different levels of consciousness as it evolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.34,0:35:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,By doing so, we've evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.53,0:35:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We've evolved a different way of conceptualizing spiritual and religious truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.71,0:35:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which I think is less pejorative, which is less traumatic,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.51,0:35:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which is less, for which there's less aversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.90,0:35:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The old, I would call it the Gothic downside of Christianity,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.92,0:35:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, was sackcloth ashes and it was built on sin and guilt and penance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.05,0:35:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Protestantism, the downside of Protestantism got it to be into the hatred of sin
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.11,0:35:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and all such stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.34,0:35:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole deal got pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.71,0:35:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Grim, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.03,0:35:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people really don't like religion that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.19,0:35:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They go because they ought to, you know, but it's because of the way in which from 200 down was contextualized.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.86,0:35:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was contextualized as sin and evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.86,0:35:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's a spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.73,0:36:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You should avoid that which makes you go weak with kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.21,0:36:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Jesus taught.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.32,0:36:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, avoid anything that makes you go weak with kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.01,0:36:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He also said,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.09,0:36:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,oppose it, avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.73,0:36:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.13,0:36:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Just do not go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.65,0:36:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.94,0:36:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to challenge the coyote dragon to a duel, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.98,0:36:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't go in his pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.40,0:36:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.67,0:36:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had a new way to contextualize what is integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.61,0:36:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we went back and reexamined religions and religions and spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.80,0:36:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and came to a different understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.25,0:36:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you recontextualize the human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.40,0:36:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the human condition, then, you can avoid the guilty self-vilification and self-hatred
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.67,0:36:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and inner fear that arises from a demonized ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.84,0:36:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to demonize the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.88,0:36:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to demonize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.86,0:37:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we recapitulate the evolution of consciousness from its first appearance on this earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.23,0:37:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it comes up through the animal kingdom, I don't have to call him evil anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.92,0:37:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to go into a sin fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.44,0:37:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to do sackcloth and ashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.96,0:37:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to do penance, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.23,0:37:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all of us arose from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.53,0:37:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't anybody here that don't have an animal body.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.65,0:37:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So why in the world would you want to go into sin and guilt over your animal nature?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.01,0:37:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, your job is to transcend your identification with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.80,0:37:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, our job here is to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.61,0:37:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So this world offers the maximum karmic opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.90,0:37:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To undo negative karma and gain positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.61,0:37:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only do that in an environment where you have the alternate options.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.53,0:38:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't purify yourself in a pure atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.44,0:38:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.96,0:38:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we'd still be on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.86,0:38:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't move there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.28,0:38:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you don't have any option.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.57,0:38:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.32,0:38:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's swell.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.92,0:38:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.34,0:38:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Great old.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.42,0:38:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where you stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.44,0:38:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you don't have any option.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.69,0:38:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.05,0:38:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.25,0:38:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.44,0:38:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got all the options now to undo that which you would like to undo from the past
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.25,0:38:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and grow and gain positive karma, positive merit, whatever you want to call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.23,0:38:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, it's egoistic, spiritual ego to seek spiritual, I mean, karmic merit for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.50,0:38:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you say, well, you do this, you get karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.50,0:38:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's sort of spiritual greediness, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.65,0:38:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a spiritual greediness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.05,0:38:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual ego said, give me karma, I mean, give me merit, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.92,0:38:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't like your bank account, so you switch it from money to your karmic bank account.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.55,0:39:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you do it because that's what you've become.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.36,0:39:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.86,0:39:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So with consciousness calibration, then, we're able to remove the mass of deception.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.94,0:39:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something what it says it is or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.51,0:39:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.19,0:39:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.71,0:39:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And this evolved, as you remember, historically, when I saw Dr. Diamond demonstrate kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.01,0:39:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just got that it wasn't a local cause and effect, the tomato on your solar plexus making your arm go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.69,0:39:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What I saw was the presentation of a stimulus to which the energy field innate to all of life either reacts positively,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.55,0:39:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, it records that it's positive, or it withdraws from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.84,0:39:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So like an amoeba, in the presence of this, goes forth and opens up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.21,0:40:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In the presence of this, he pulls back.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.07,0:40:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness must have learned, for the sake of survival on this planet, how to differentiate truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.65,0:40:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can look at it as almost a protoplasmic wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.51,0:40:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like protoplasm knows what's inimical to its survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.65,0:40:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it also...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.53,0:40:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And to it's that which is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.40,0:40:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, life had to be able to gain and integrate information.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.15,0:40:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how intelligence arose.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.11,0:40:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligence arose in the nonlinear field of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.34,0:40:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't arise in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.05,0:40:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It expresses itself as genes and chromosomes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.34,0:40:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's only the expression of that which is on a different realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.78,0:40:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is not the realm of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.11,0:40:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.59,0:40:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with a basic understanding, you then become stunningly aware
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.40,0:40:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that evolution and creation are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.82,0:41:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how the dualistic mind would like to set them as creationism, you know, creation versus evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.71,0:41:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and then take an egoistic stand on which one is the truth and attack the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.38,0:41:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see how duality, you know, leads to conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.26,0:41:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution and creation are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.09,0:41:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, evolution is nothing but the unfolding of creation, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.82,0:41:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That gives you a different context in which to perceive all of experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.61,0:41:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, instead of seeing it as cause and effect of this causing of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.48,0:41:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what you see is the unfolding of an emergence of a potentiality into an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.71,0:41:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,when local conditions are favorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.59,0:41:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not even seeing change.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.61,0:41:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not seeing change.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.30,0:41:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.48,0:41:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.50,0:41:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.53,0:41:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This pupa in the chrysalis is not changing into a butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.51,0:41:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't a pupa anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.21,0:42:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.03,0:42:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the potentiality becomes an actuality when the conditions are appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.98,0:42:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.61,0:42:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.98,0:42:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's emerging as its potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.11,0:42:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at a certain level of consciousness, you don't see anything changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.78,0:42:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is just automatically evolving as the consequence of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.94,0:42:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything positions itself within the infinite field of consciousness as a consequence of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.36,0:42:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the karmic propensities then tend to define that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.59,0:42:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which you are will determine how you respond in the overall, you might call it, electromagnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.63,0:42:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I use the analogy that we're like little iron filings.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.09,0:42:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the best analogy, but in a giant electromagnetic field,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.34,0:43:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see where that little thing positions itself depends not only on the power of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.42,0:43:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but on how its charge is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.19,0:43:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a lot of positive at this end of his little iron filing and a lot of negative at the other end.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.36,0:43:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he's going to position himself depending on what he's become.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.01,0:43:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the more you align yourself with truth, you're going to obviously move as a consequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.01,0:43:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,not of causality, not of an arbitrary capricious God,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.23,0:43:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but as a consequence of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.69,0:43:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Who you've become, you automatically align, become aligned by the power of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.46,0:43:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of the field is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.59,0:43:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, God's justice is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.23,0:43:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,God's justice is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.90,0:43:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing can happen to you by anything outside of yourself, but only because of what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.76,0:43:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Only by your own ascent and your own free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.11,0:43:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that divine justice?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.65,0:43:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's divine justice beyond any description I've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.23,0:43:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.57,0:44:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's so clearly obvious, it's just stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.75,0:44:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.42,0:44:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All comes about then as a consequence of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.92,0:44:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.44,0:44:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What it is, is its meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.36,0:44:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.40,0:44:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what this means.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.65,0:44:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can see it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.11,0:44:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What it is is what it means, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.90,0:44:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.36,0:44:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That avoids the...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.59,0:44:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That avoids the dualistic split between res interna mentation and res externa, the world as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.36,0:44:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we do is we transcend that dualistic split and approach it from the viewpoint of non-duality, which is not subject to such error.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.71,0:44:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.05,0:45:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So we then calibrated, we ended up with a scale of consciousness in which it goes from one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.67,0:45:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,One is the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.48,0:45:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,One is the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.53,0:45:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,One is the beginning of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.30,0:45:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And 1,000 is the maximum level of consciousness possible in this domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.34,0:45:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a logarithmic scale because the numbers go up mathematically very rapidly and they get so big you can't handle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.65,0:45:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So then it dawned on me, wow, use logarithms.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.92,0:45:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.26,0:45:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,With logarithms, it came out really great.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.67,0:45:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,From one to a thousand, I'm a market gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.09,0:45:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So we asked, what has ever existed on this planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.42,0:45:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest calibration of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.51,0:45:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And this was 1,000 and it was the great avatars, Christ and Buddha and Zoroaster and Krishna, the great beings who have set the paradigm of reality for mankind down through the centuries, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.59,0:45:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,One to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.26,0:46:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we found with presenting a stimulus with kinesiology, and as I repeat, you can't have any vested interest in the answer, the two people have to be integrous people, and their intention has to be,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.21,0:46:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and the best way to achieve that is to ask questions in the name of the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.86,0:46:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to work for ABZ company.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.11,0:46:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Working, so you check ABZ company, I have permission to ask about, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.11,0:46:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it an integrous company?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.11,0:46:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.11,0:46:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,ABC company calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.11,0:46:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.11,0:46:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.51,0:46:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.51,0:46:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I accepting this job would serve the highest good?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.51,0:46:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.75,0:46:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.75,0:46:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.51,0:46:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.51,0:46:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.51,0:46:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.86,0:46:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can either ask or not ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.86,0:46:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.92,0:46:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you can start asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.92,0:46:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you find out, after you've asked a dozen questions, it isn't the money, it isn't the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.11,0:46:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,sun, then you ask, would I fit in with the crowd there?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.15,0:47:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.15,0:47:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.69,0:47:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You just wouldn't fit in with those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.69,0:47:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See, you don't know that as a person, but the infinite field knows that, because it's
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.94,0:47:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,not limited in time and space.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.94,0:47:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say, in the name of the highest good, this would be a great job.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.94,0:47:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This would be a great job for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.94,0:47:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get no.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.94,0:47:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you got yeses on everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.94,0:47:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the explanation?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.23,0:47:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You can either just accept it and say, look, God said no, so the heck with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.23,0:47:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you can check it out as to why the no.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.23,0:47:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's, see, when you ask in the name of the highest good, you forget the highest good
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.61,0:47:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,includes you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.61,0:47:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, well, I'm interested in, you know, whether I'm going to succeed on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.61,0:47:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.61,0:47:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the highest good is you're included in the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.61,0:47:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.61,0:47:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Your misery is not going to serve the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.61,0:47:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got to know, because it's not the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.61,0:47:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.61,0:47:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So that saves you going there, appearing to be a bumpkin, getting thrown out, because
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.61,0:47:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't fit in with the crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.61,0:47:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.82,0:48:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to run into that periodically as a door-to-door salesman selling vacuum cleaners
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.65,0:48:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and stuff, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.65,0:48:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I just wasn't glib and without any scruples.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.84,0:48:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I was a great canvasser.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.26,0:48:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I could get into anybody's house, because I was benign and innocuous, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.67,0:48:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'd let me in, you know, but I couldn't close the deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.67,0:48:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So to close the deal, you had to call in a closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.96,0:48:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the closer would nail him up against the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.15,0:48:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I'd say, she's going to get a divorce if her husband don't pay for this vacuum cleaner.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.15,0:48:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was not a closer, you know, not a closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.15,0:48:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.50,0:48:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.50,0:48:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're designed for the job or not, see, is something I wouldn't know experientially.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.50,0:48:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I'd used that before selling vacuum cleaners house-to-house, I would have said,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.50,0:49:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I thought, what was I selling?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.50,0:49:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What was Kirby vacuum cleaners?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.50,0:49:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, Kirby vacuum cleaners is Integra's.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.50,0:49:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they're a great vacuum cleaner.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.50,0:49:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And this, it would serve that as good for me to take this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.50,0:49:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have gotten a no.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.50,0:49:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Save myself all that misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.50,0:49:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.50,0:49:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it has a very pragmatic use.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.50,0:49:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's just go back to the scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.50,0:49:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this scale we readdressed a number of times because it's a common point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.50,0:49:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's relatively simple and straightforward.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.50,0:49:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it covers different ways of looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.50,0:49:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,These are different levels of the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.50,0:49:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not the evolution of good and bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.50,0:49:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't mean this down here is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.69,0:49:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Experientially, it's bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.69,0:49:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not bad-bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.69,0:49:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean this is good and this is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.69,0:49:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What it means is this is how life evolves from the most primitive to the most advanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.69,0:50:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And how it evolved over great periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.69,0:50:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's extremely useful from a pragmatic viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.30,0:50:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the book Truth vs. Falsehood is an examination of the pragmatic utility of having a means of discerning truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.30,0:50:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And none of that but the calibrated level.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.30,0:50:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What do all these things in our world, throughout history and our current world, what do they reflect and what can be learned out of that that is helpful to the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.44,0:50:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One of my biggest intentions out of this book would be that it would create for the first time a science of diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.44,0:50:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A science of diplomacy whereby peace could prevail.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.44,0:50:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The history of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.44,0:50:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind has been at war 93% of the history of civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.44,0:50:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only been at peace 7%.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.86,0:51:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do the calibrated scale of consciousness then on an international diplomacy level,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.86,0:51:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you make discoveries that are really aha.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.86,0:51:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You instantly see what the problem is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.86,0:51:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.86,0:51:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A kindergartner could practically see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.86,0:51:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's all these erudite people and all this money and pomp and all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.86,0:51:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's falling on its butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.86,0:51:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.86,0:51:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer is really simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.86,0:51:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's so simple that it's sort of pathetic to arrive at what the answer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.86,0:51:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We've actually done it for some countries that were really on the edge of ballistic war, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.86,0:51:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, within an hour you got an answer to the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.86,0:51:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Within three days the whole deal is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.86,0:51:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's hugging everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.86,0:51:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all in the papers and harmony prevails.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.86,0:51:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a pragmatic application of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.96,0:51:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was a unique example because we had a bunch of congressmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.96,0:51:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They were not just politicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.96,0:51:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They were statesmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.96,0:51:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They were statesmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.36,0:51:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And they sat there in great wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.36,0:52:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember we had a whole bunch of members of the Congress and other important people.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.36,0:52:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And Susan and I were trying to answer all these questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.55,0:52:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I look at them and they all look like Buddhas.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.55,0:52:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see any vociferous arm waving.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.63,0:52:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see veins standing on their neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.63,0:52:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't get right and wrong and all this crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.94,0:52:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just time to say they're going hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.80,0:52:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight or ten people all going hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.11,0:52:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we calibrated the response to different moves on the part of this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.59,0:52:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What would be the response to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.59,0:52:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we came up with a simplistic, simplistic solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.80,0:52:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Simplistic solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.84,0:52:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if I got permission to reveal the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.84,0:52:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to reveal the solution to this audience who resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.32,0:52:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to reveal the solution to this audience who resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.76,0:53:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it was a rather obvious solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.92,0:53:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just using it as a pragmatic, pragmatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.86,0:53:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But it did work and history attests to that fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.00,0:53:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.00,0:53:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is very practically useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.00,0:53:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world, of course the original design was not about the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.11,0:53:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The original design had to do with pursuing spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.11,0:53:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a psychiatrist I was interested in emotionality, the levels of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.11,0:53:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been psychoanalyzed in Columbia Psychoanalytic.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.11,0:53:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And these were called the emergency emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.11,0:53:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And these were called the welfare emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.67,0:53:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are calibrated in accordance with the perennial wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.67,0:53:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Repetitiously throughout all of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.67,0:53:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears in many forms in all cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.67,0:53:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's corroboration by collective human experience over great eons of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.67,0:54:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as psychoanalytic principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.67,0:54:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychology and psychiatry.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.67,0:54:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And these levels are reaffirmed when we start calibrating the levels of truth in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.92,0:54:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.92,0:54:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.44,0:54:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We get that the serial killer calibrates around 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.44,0:54:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.44,0:54:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He does, serial killer 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.65,0:54:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,About 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.65,0:54:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,About 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.01,0:54:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We get that Mother Teresa calibrates over 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.07,0:54:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.07,0:54:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,750 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.07,0:54:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother Teresa calibrates at 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.07,0:54:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's rather obvious, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.07,0:54:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The serial killer is not up here and Mother Teresa is not down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.07,0:54:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So it sort of reaffirms.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.07,0:54:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you do this thousands of times, you recontextualize the totality of the human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.48,0:54:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.48,0:55:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's move on to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.48,0:55:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to just, because for the new people we want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.48,0:55:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to know what time we have the break time.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.98,0:55:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I got a better hustle.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.07,0:55:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.07,0:55:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to do a little different.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.07,0:55:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico is going to chant before lunch instead of before the question and answer period.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.07,0:55:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he has to leave early.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.07,0:55:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's doing a spiritual thing workshop elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.07,0:55:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.34,0:55:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So we recalibrate then.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.34,0:55:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We reaffirm the reality of divinity itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.88,0:55:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of skeptics, atheists.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.96,0:55:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Various people don't believe in God.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.96,0:55:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.96,0:55:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So are they correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.96,0:55:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.96,0:55:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The level is about 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.42,0:55:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The skeptic, the atheist, et cetera, is not really a high level.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.51,0:55:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The agnostic is a much higher level of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.51,0:55:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,See, agnosticism, you say, frankly, of myself, I don't know the reality whether God exists or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.51,0:55:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's truthful.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.51,0:56:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.51,0:56:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To say that God doesn't exist is pretty grandiose.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.51,0:56:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody knows that God doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.90,0:56:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fallacious statement to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.32,0:56:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.82,0:56:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So humility then, even though you don't know, you're still being honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.82,0:56:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can recalibrate and verify all the great states of consciousness reported throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.82,0:56:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.17,0:56:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The enlightened condition, the advanced mystical states, illuminated conditions, have been reported from,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.17,0:56:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,everywhere on the globe, all different cultures since at least 5000 BC.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.32,0:56:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And these various cultures are separated from each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.32,0:56:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet each inner experience, each mystic reports exactly the same inner revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.42,0:57:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's revalidated outside of cultures, outside of belief systems, outside of ethnic identifications, outside of religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.65,0:57:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.65,0:57:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how the levels of consciousness are distributed in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.65,0:57:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you see the world as a land of great opportunity, then you can live with this fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.28,0:57:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,78% of the world's population calibrates below the level of 200, below the level of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.67,0:57:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it is a difficult world to live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.67,0:57:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not a celestial realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.92,0:57:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's naive romantic people who think that we should convert this to a celestial realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.86,0:57:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.86,0:57:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.00,0:57:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is supposed to be a celestial realm, it would be, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.00,0:58:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it was a celestial realm, why would you be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.38,0:58:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Ramana Maharishi said,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.44,0:58:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in trying to save the world, because the world you see doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.44,0:58:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's how you conceptualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.44,0:58:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So the average human mind laments this condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.44,0:58:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that this much of the population calibrates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.63,0:58:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's why this is a world of maximum karmic opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.30,0:58:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you have here all choices from the lowest.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.30,0:58:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.30,0:58:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.30,0:58:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can try and save them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.30,0:58:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.30,0:58:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can bless them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.30,0:58:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can curse them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.30,0:58:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of those is going to move your little magnetic filing somewhere in the electrostatic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.59,0:58:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate you, you son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.59,0:58:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.59,0:58:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You just went down.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.59,0:58:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, Socrates said,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.63,0:58:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,man chooses only the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.63,0:59:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, this man is doing what he thinks is the best thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.63,0:59:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Your little iron filing just moved up.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.63,0:59:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.63,0:59:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgiveness, the course of miracles, 12 steps, how they work.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.26,0:59:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.26,0:59:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you see, the reason man has not exterminated himself
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.26,0:59:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is because the power of the people at the top of the pyramid,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.26,0:59:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,their power overbalances.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.26,0:59:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside is 78% below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.26,0:59:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So above 200, you have levels of power,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.30,0:59:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and below 200, you have levels of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.30,0:59:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, only a few people on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.36,0:59:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,only half a dozen on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.36,0:59:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrate extremely high,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.36,0:59:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalance the total negativity of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.36,0:59:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.48,0:59:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've asked with kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.48,0:59:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,if it weren't for those people near the top,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.90,0:59:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind would have self-destructed eons ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.90,0:59:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we got yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.90,0:59:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He would have self-destructed eons ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.90,1:00:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But because there is that paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.63,1:00:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that power of truth prevailing,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.63,1:00:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the evolution of consciousness sent to us by a student.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.63,1:00:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And it just shows, people ask this often,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.63,1:00:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what about the future and all the prophecies of the future,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.63,1:00:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,which all calibrate below 200, by the way?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.63,1:00:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's going to end in 682.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.73,1:00:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.73,1:00:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.73,1:00:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the UFO religions all calibrate low.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.73,1:00:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm over 20.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.73,1:00:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.73,1:00:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is how consciousness is evolving over time.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.00,1:00:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see, this is where it is now.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.00,1:00:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the future of mankind is not cataclysmic,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.15,1:00:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,apocalyptic, whatever they predict all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.44,1:00:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, you see that the level of consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.63,1:00:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is now advancing more and more and more rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.63,1:00:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.96,1:00:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't forget that evolution leads to revolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.15,1:01:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, well, if man's evolving,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.15,1:01:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,shouldn't we have peace all the time everywhere
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.15,1:01:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and no poverty and all that?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.15,1:01:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.15,1:01:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, too much Kool-Aid, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.03,1:01:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They have that Kool-Aid.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.03,1:01:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ said the same thing, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.03,1:01:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As evolution advances, we saw the change in the corporate America.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.03,1:01:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When the calibrated level of consciousness went over,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.03,1:01:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it was at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.03,1:01:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was at 190 for eons.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.03,1:01:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it went up to 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.07,1:01:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's 207.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.07,1:01:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortly after the level of consciousness went from 190 to 205 and then 207,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.07,1:01:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you saw the great fraudulent corporations hit the decks.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.07,1:01:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest names in corporate business, giant accounting firms.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.07,1:01:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, they were like, you know, a Wall Street bank collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.46,1:01:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.46,1:01:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see evolution then brought forth integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.59,1:01:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as the new principle of success.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.59,1:02:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, on the level of integrity, this was not success anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.59,1:02:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, that was collapse.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.59,1:02:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, evolution tends to bring revolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.90,1:02:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You certainly saw legal revolution on Wall Street.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.00,1:02:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Giant firms, Rural Comm and Enron.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.00,1:02:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember the name of them all because I don't follow the business news.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.00,1:02:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But they fell one after another.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.00,1:02:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Catastrophic.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.00,1:02:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But you could get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.13,1:02:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,190, you cannot get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.13,1:02:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,207, you cannot get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.13,1:02:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level 207.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.13,1:02:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get away with it temporarily.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.13,1:02:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But the field is now so high, it's going to surface you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.13,1:02:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sooner or later, the field is going to surface you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.13,1:02:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be able to hide in the shadows because you might say the light has gone up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.15,1:02:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the light of truth has gone up,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.15,1:02:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,darkness can no longer survive with equal facility.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.15,1:02:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to recapitulate the evolution of life on this planet since the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.19,1:03:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,These are archeologic ages that run into billions of eons, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.19,1:03:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see the level of consciousness of life over the eons.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.92,1:03:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Back here, so far prehistoric that I can't even conceptualize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.92,1:03:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximately rock creation in millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.23,1:03:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And you run into billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.23,1:03:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, the evolution of life that you see begins way back in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.28,1:03:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrated as one, and then two, and then on up.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.28,1:03:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And it exhibits itself in the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.28,1:03:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So life started very primitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.28,1:03:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.28,1:03:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I want to get to the core of the point we're making this morning before the break.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.28,1:03:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In the animal kingdom, you can track the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.63,1:03:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,See, this has got nothing to do with sin and guilt, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.63,1:03:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.63,1:04:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how life evolved, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.63,1:04:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.80,1:04:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts out here, one, bacteria, protozoa.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.80,1:04:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,On up through the octopus, sharks, Komodo dragon, reptiles, snakes, alligators, dinosaurs, whales, dolphins.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.15,1:04:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,On up through the birds of prey, rhinoceros.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.19,1:04:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not too friendly sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.40,1:04:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Water buffaloes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.40,1:04:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Very dangerous water buffaloes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.40,1:04:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out for water buffaloes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.96,1:04:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They look like they're not paying attention to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.96,1:04:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They're fooling you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.96,1:04:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you try to walk behind them, and they're fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.96,1:04:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I'm just worried about water buffaloes and you folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.03,1:04:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Wolves, hippopotamus, they kill a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.03,1:04:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippopotamus kills a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.03,1:04:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly, all of a sudden, level 200, you see you go from the carnivore to the herbivore.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.21,1:04:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all herbivores.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.21,1:05:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,200 and up.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.28,1:05:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the same thing happens in the animal kingdom as in the human kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.28,1:05:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200 and up, you have a totally different way.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.28,1:05:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the herbivore, who doesn't have to kill anything, doesn't live by predation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.28,1:05:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It just eats grass and fertilizes the grass back, and so it's mutually beneficial, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.34,1:05:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you come on up through the evolution of the animal kingdom, up through chimpanzees,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.63,1:05:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you have these unique expressions as the dog's wagging tail and the cat's purr,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.63,1:05:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,which are peculiarly at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.63,1:05:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safer with a dog than 78% of the people on the population.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.69,1:05:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a cruel fact, but it is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.36,1:05:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd rather be in a cage with a gorilla than 78% of the people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.90,1:06:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A mountain gorilla just eats his stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.50,1:06:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if you don't go and hassle him or try and steal his baby, you're just another being, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.01,1:06:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.01,1:06:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the expression of the evolution of consciousness, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.03,1:06:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And that brings us to the essential point I want to make before we take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.03,1:06:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we take a break?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.03,1:06:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,11.15?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.03,1:06:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we've got to save some minutes to save your soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.03,1:06:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.03,1:06:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to reconstruct spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.05,1:06:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it outside of the Gothic paradigm of sin and guilt, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.34,1:06:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what you saw in the evolution of consciousness there had nothing to do with sin and guilt, did it?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.34,1:06:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It had to do with how far you evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.34,1:06:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.53,1:06:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes from predacious to non-predacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.65,1:06:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Life in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.90,1:07:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the beginning, out of the unmanifest arose the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.90,1:07:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The light of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.90,1:07:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then interacted with matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.94,1:07:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the interaction of the light of divinity, the radiance of divinity, and the interaction of matter arises the potentiality for life.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.28,1:07:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So life is, the essence of life is of divine origin.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.28,1:07:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why life cannot be killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.28,1:07:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot kill life.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.28,1:07:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can force it to move into different expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.80,1:07:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you cannot kill it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.80,1:07:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.00,1:07:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you'd be killing God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.00,1:07:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even kill life.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.00,1:07:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You just kill God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.00,1:07:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,God and life, that is the source.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.00,1:07:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The radiance of divinity is life.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.00,1:07:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So then this life, in order to succeed on this planet, has to know survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.05,1:07:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So it has to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.05,1:08:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the point I'm trying to make this morning is that the ego is your gettingness that comes out of the evolution of consciousness and its expression in the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.05,1:08:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you didn't know how to get, you wouldn't be here today to feel guilty about getting.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.09,1:08:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,For life to survive, then, these primitive things have to know, be able to probe, probe their environment.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.38,1:08:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to be able to process whether it's good or bad, biochemically, is it biologically beneficial, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.38,1:08:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So life comes about, then, as a consequence of getting.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.07,1:08:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where we're, when we're stuck on our solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.07,1:08:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.07,1:08:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it evolves to the animal kingdom in which your survival depends on getting.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.07,1:08:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.78,1:08:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego is the basis of your animal, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.46,1:08:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,To survive, you have to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.46,1:08:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll notice everything about your ego has to do with get, whether it's pride, whether it's grief.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.46,1:08:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You just look, grief is you just lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.46,1:09:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's competition, rivalry, you see, because as animal life evolves, you go into tribal, your survival depends on the tribe, the wolf pack, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.46,1:09:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are still expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.46,1:09:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Some other wolf pack poaches on your territory.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.46,1:09:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're at war.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.46,1:09:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So war is the automatic evolution, then, of the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.46,1:09:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.46,1:09:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just the same as the warring factions of primitive man, primitive men, being dominated by the survival mechanisms of the animal brain, which, of course, is on one side of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.25,1:09:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you get above level 200, you get the inpouring of Kundalini spiritual energy, which changes your brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.25,1:09:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see and experience the world differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.82,1:09:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The predominance of this evolutionary history within the human psyche is what religion calls sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.27,1:10:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If it predominates, you're sinful.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.18,1:10:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you learn to transcend it, then you're not sinful.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.18,1:10:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But what has sackcloth and ashes got to do with it?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.18,1:10:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Not really anything, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.18,1:10:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's thought to be a learning tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.18,1:10:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes, it's thought to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.18,1:10:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And at a certain level, it is a learning tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.18,1:10:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's very pragmatic for sort of primitive evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.18,1:10:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's only at level 200 that other people's existence becomes significant to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.68,1:10:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, other people are only to be used for your own personal gain, for your popularity, your winning an election, making more money, sexual satisfaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.76,1:10:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the animal is always predacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.76,1:10:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is what religion calls sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.01,1:11:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If you see it now as the persistence of animal survival behavior when it's no longer appropriate, then you have a different way to contextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.07,1:11:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,People don't want to look at their downside because it brings up guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.07,1:11:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.19,1:11:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And that guilt is endemic to traditional religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.19,1:11:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In psychoanalysis, the first premise is to undo the patient's punitive superego.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.39,1:11:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you start pulling up what's in the unconscious, the superego, which is the conscience, tends to be sadistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.81,1:11:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to ameliorate and become a reasonable conscience that accepts the fact you're human.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.81,1:11:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you do make mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.81,1:11:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.81,1:11:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You learn and go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.81,1:11:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you don't have to savage yourself about every little character defect that you discover within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.81,1:11:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So what brings that about is the alliance between the patient and the analyst.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.90,1:11:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you say, you know, you don't say anything for about 10 minutes, and they go, okay, all right, now come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.90,1:12:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So you tell them, well, and then you recall something from childhood in which you're very embarrassed and in chagrin and shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.90,1:12:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the analyst says, well, of course you did that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.44,1:12:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, of course you did that, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.44,1:12:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All children are that way, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.44,1:12:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All children get into sex play.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.44,1:12:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So you, you know, so you play doctor and nurse with the eight-year-old next door.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.44,1:12:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, try telling that to your analyst, you know, when you're a mature adult about how you play doctor and nurse with the eight-year-old next door.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.44,1:12:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good when you're sitting up all by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.51,1:12:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You try laying it down, and then what are you thinking about, Doc, Dave, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.31,1:12:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking about the eight-year-old girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.31,1:12:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.31,1:12:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The eight-year-old down the block.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.31,1:12:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're playing doctor and nurse.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.78,1:12:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you feel chagrin, shame, embarrassment, guilt, all about your animal, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.19,1:12:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ex-sexual curiosity, which is part of the animal, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.19,1:13:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So when your analyst says, well, of course that's natural and evolutionary, and every kid's curious about what the hell it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.19,1:13:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think they ought to be?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.19,1:13:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all of a sudden your sadistic superego becomes more rational now, and you can look at yourself without savaging yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.19,1:13:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So I like to recontextualize all this, and I'm doing it again today.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.48,1:13:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This contextualization makes the inner honesty that's required for spiritual evolution a more benign experience, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.52,1:13:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have a benign view of your little animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.52,1:13:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I keep repeating, without your animal, you wouldn't be here to, you know, to feel guilty about your animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.52,1:13:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've got a shift.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.52,1:13:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Period.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.52,1:13:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a shift paradigm from this being real to this being of a higher value.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.52,1:13:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like, you know, whether I'm supposed to treat this patient, cure this patient, or please my colleagues, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.59,1:13:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's the two paradigms you've got to choose, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.59,1:13:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I want approval by my colleagues?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.59,1:14:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Or when I face God, do I want to be accountable that I, you know, refuse to do what I know would help this guy, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.72,1:14:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He was committing suicide every time.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.28,1:14:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time he got on a hypoglycemic episode, in and out of the hospital, suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.71,1:14:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some people with blood sugars, so if they eat a lot of sugar, you know, their blood sugar goes out like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.71,1:14:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it'll shoot down like this, whammo, in a matter of hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.71,1:14:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're shaking, and they will go into a rage.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.71,1:14:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll go into a rage.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.11,1:14:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Irrational rage.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.11,1:14:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Or they'll get drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.11,1:14:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Or they'll hit somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.11,1:14:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Or they'll commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.11,1:14:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Or they'll get depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.11,1:14:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, everybody had poo-pooed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.11,1:14:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.11,1:14:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Functional hypoglycemia.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.11,1:14:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember a friend of mine who put me up for an exclusive club.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.47,1:14:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He had the worst case of functional hypoglycemia I ever saw.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.72,1:14:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He weighed over 450 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.72,1:14:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And was periodically drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.92,1:14:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I counseled him.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.92,1:15:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He stood off sugar and sweets.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.92,1:15:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Got sober.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.92,1:15:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Was doing fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.01,1:15:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Began to enlarge his business.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.10,1:15:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he saw a lady doctor in New York City who poo-pooed hypoglycemia.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.72,1:15:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that's what he was looking for.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.72,1:15:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't hoping.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.88,1:15:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And he went back.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.88,1:15:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you could tell he had hypoglycemia.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.88,1:15:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because anything sweet on a table, he was, like, riveted to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.88,1:15:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He was, like, riveted to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.88,1:15:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he had a voracious craving for sugar, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.19,1:15:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And he died some months later.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.19,1:15:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He went back to sugar and died.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.19,1:15:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.19,1:15:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, academically, hypoglycemia probably still isn't acceptable.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.52,1:15:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that it can cost you your life to not know the difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.52,1:15:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It can cost you your life, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.52,1:15:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,People with functional hypoglycemia can become, I've seen them get catatonic.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.52,1:15:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told you the story about this patient having the glucose tolerance test in the laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.52,1:16:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the guy that ran the lab was a big, tall, skinny guy with a long, white lab coat, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.52,1:16:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And her blood sugar shoots down to, like, I don't know, 86 or 92 or 80, 40 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.52,1:16:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they were in the fifth hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.52,1:16:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Shot down like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.52,1:16:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At one point, she tore off all her clothes, ran naked down the street in Northern Boulevard
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.52,1:16:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in Manhattan, New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.52,1:16:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a busy boulevard.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.52,1:16:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Stark naked.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.52,1:16:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She pulls this off.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.52,1:16:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She's totally irrational.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.52,1:16:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Running naked down the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.52,1:16:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Cars all banging against each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.02,1:16:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's the lab director, like Ichabod Crane, 6'6", and all skinny, this white coat
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.02,1:16:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,flying behind him.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.02,1:16:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back, Ms. Cormack.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.02,1:16:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back, Ms. Cormack.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.02,1:16:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,His coat's on.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.02,1:16:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,She's running wildly.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.02,1:16:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He's running after her.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.02,1:16:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.43,1:16:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So you better believe clinical science.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.43,1:16:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Academic science is good for an orientation, but you can't live with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.43,1:16:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't live with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.43,1:17:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't perforate your ulcer because people don't believe in acupuncture.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.43,1:17:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't go into a psychotic state and get hospitalized and commit suicide and murder.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.47,1:17:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminals, they'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.47,1:17:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to have to go into a rage, punch somebody out, and the guy dies.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.65,1:17:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He's still in prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.65,1:17:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All he had to do was get off sugar and sweets.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.14,1:17:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd be a free man.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.14,1:17:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.14,1:17:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're trying to give you a realistic viewpoint of what can you really trust in this world,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.32,1:17:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because you'll see the focus of the news is always on what's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.32,1:17:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the truth in Aruba?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.32,1:17:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the truth in Iraq?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.32,1:17:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the truth in Porsche?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.32,1:17:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.32,1:17:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.32,1:17:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, we have a means of discerning truth from falsehood, and to me, it's a gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.32,1:17:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a gift from consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.32,1:17:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.32,1:17:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.32,1:17:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a gift from consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.32,1:17:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like, karmically, we've evolved to the point where we've earned the gift for those
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.32,1:18:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,who are at least integrous to have the means of discerning truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.32,1:18:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,First time in all of our life.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.72,1:18:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-three percent of the time, man's been at war.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.72,1:18:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.72,1:18:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know whether this is a great leader or a case of malignant, messianic narcissism
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.72,1:18:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates at 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.72,1:18:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't tell.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.13,1:18:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A great leader.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.13,1:18:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Napoleon, in the beginning, was like at 440 or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.15,1:18:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he crashed, and that was Waterloo.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.15,1:18:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can't tell the difference between a great leader, an Eisenhower, or a Bin Laden.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.84,1:18:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a calendar, you can't tell what day it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.84,1:18:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a compass, you don't know which direction you're going.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.84,1:18:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've got a compass for the first time in human history, for which I am grateful
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.84,1:18:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and thankful.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.84,1:18:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I give thanks for mankind to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.84,1:18:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.84,1:18:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.84,1:18:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're going to take a break, and we're going to reconvene in 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.84,1:19:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.15,1:19:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, you've got to move fast in 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.15,1:19:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.27,1:19:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We're ready to resume.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.59,1:19:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.59,1:19:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's always new people, we tried to recapitulate the evolution of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.59,1:19:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,how it expresses itself in life.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.59,1:19:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried to recontextualize the nature of the ego itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.64,1:19:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is so central to all society.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.64,1:19:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so central to all spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.15,1:19:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And reinterpret it in the light of history, to avoid the Gothic downside of religion,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.15,1:19:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which causes a certain aversion to religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.15,1:19:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, a lot of people avoid it, because they just don't want to look at guilt and
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.15,1:19:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.15,1:19:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the 12-step groups, the fourth step is, first step, you admit you're powerless
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.42,1:19:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,without God's help.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.42,1:19:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, in the fourth step, you take a fearless inner inventory.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.77,1:19:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people get that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.77,1:20:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people get sober and stay sober up to step three, and never do step four.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.31,1:20:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Took an honest and thorough spiritual inventory, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.38,1:20:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And why do people avoid that?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.38,1:20:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They avoid that because of the way the ego's been contextualized.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.38,1:20:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with a different contextualization, you can see what all you're saying is, the primitive
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.18,1:20:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,drives within the human brain, because they're genetically there, imprinted, you know, in
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.18,1:20:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,time and chromosomes and all, and genes, tend to dominate, unless there's some reason
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.03,1:20:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to go beyond them, or go beyond them.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.03,1:20:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the big jump is honesty and owning responsibility for one's own actions.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.47,1:20:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,To take responsibility for one's own actions.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.47,1:20:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,To be innocent reduces culpability, but that does not eliminate responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.25,1:21:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fine point.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.25,1:21:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact you didn't know reduces culpability, but the fact that you've got to undo that,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.67,1:21:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you've still got to undo it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.67,1:21:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you owe the money not through any fault of your own, you still owe the money
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.67,1:21:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to the bank.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.67,1:21:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,See what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.67,1:21:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, on the other hand, your punishability is down to zero, but you're still your responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.69,1:21:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to take responsibility for your own decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.69,1:21:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.85,1:21:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The human is driven by fallacy, because of the distortion of the animal brain, but he
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.85,1:21:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,still is responsible for his actions and to evolve beyond them.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.85,1:21:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is possible to do it without your superego, which is your Freudian conscience, attacking
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.92,1:21:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.92,1:21:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're relatively...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.07,1:22:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're relatively unafraid of your own conscience, then you can do an honest and
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.07,1:22:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous inner spiritual inventory.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.07,1:22:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it looks like it's a dangerous animal waiting to bite you the minute you admit something,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.07,1:22:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.07,1:22:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to avoid that denial and aversion to inner honesty, I think recontextualizing the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.07,1:22:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.07,1:22:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.07,1:22:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.32,1:22:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing I tried to do was also integrate spiritual reality, consciousness reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.64,1:22:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness research with prevailing physics and the intellectual paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.64,1:22:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And of great interest to us in spiritual work is the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.64,1:22:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.64,1:22:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Heisenberg principle is very critical.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.80,1:22:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the state of the universe, the state of the universe, any condition, you can calculate
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.80,1:22:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Schrodinger equations, which are both time dependent and time independent.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.80,1:23:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Which has a significance also.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.06,1:23:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, by introducing consciousness, you change and you collapse the wave function from potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.53,1:23:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,into actuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.53,1:23:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the concordance of quantum theory and Heisenberg principle and spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.53,1:23:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, you know, at a certain level, all you see is everything actualizing its potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.76,1:23:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when local conditions are correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.82,1:23:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one local condition is intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.82,1:23:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the Heisenberg principle is the mathematical abstract about sub-particle physics explaining
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.96,1:23:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,how the universe works at a much deeper level than the strictly measurable linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.96,1:23:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's of extreme importance because intention, intention, alignment with integrity and truth
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.05,1:23:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,then makes possible, makes possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.31,1:24:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, your spiritual intention then realigns and changes the way you see options and choices.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.84,1:24:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual commitment then collapses the wave function so that the potential becomes actual.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.84,1:24:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how you become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.84,1:24:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just do the Heisenberg principle over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.76,1:24:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what prayer does.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.76,1:24:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the supplication.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.76,1:24:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Turning the prayer wheel.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.76,1:24:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book, you'll see most of those things, which Westerners laugh at, calibrate quite
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.76,1:24:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,high.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.76,1:24:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.76,1:24:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the power of the intention of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.76,1:24:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention of turning the prayer wheel is appealing to God, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.80,1:24:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's got nothing to do with the mechanics of turning the prayer wheel.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.80,1:24:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with the intention which empowers it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.80,1:24:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the Heisenberg principle then is a correlation between the scientific paradigm and spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.31,1:24:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,work.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.65,1:24:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention facilitates transformation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.65,1:25:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Your intention to be devoted to truth and to serve God through all the various yogas
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.85,1:25:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever means is what accounts for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.85,1:25:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, some people reach very advanced states even though they're following sort of fallacious
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.92,1:25:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,teachings and practices because of the purity of their intention, the purity of their intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.92,1:25:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, purity of their intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.17,1:25:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Heisenberg principle then introduces.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.17,1:25:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, that's where Einstein rebelled.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.17,1:25:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, you see, Einstein calibrates at 499, genius and brilliance, and himself religious.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.10,1:25:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you remember, as I've said before, he rebelled at the Heisenberg principle because
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.13,1:25:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he preferred to think that there was a universe out there independent of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.13,1:25:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.13,1:25:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Which, of course, was just a preference.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.35,1:26:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But, what that means is he bucked, he bucked.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.35,1:26:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because the 400s is a paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.35,1:26:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And then from 500 and up is a different paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.35,1:26:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It runs by different rules.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.35,1:26:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from, it evolves from a wholly different source.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.35,1:26:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In science today, many, you know, science and theology, news and all those things, you'll
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.69,1:26:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,see they calibrate in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.69,1:26:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What they're trying to do is define the reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.69,1:26:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality, spiritual reality and religious truth in terms that are appropriate to the
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.52,1:26:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.52,1:26:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't define the 500s in the terminology and conceptualization that's appropriate for
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.52,1:26:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,science.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.52,1:26:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask me what is the relationship between science and religion, I'll tell you flat out.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.52,1:26:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There ain't any.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.52,1:26:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There ain't any.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.52,1:26:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They're two different, totally different paradigms of what is truth, how do you arrive at truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.35,1:27:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Science and theology, right, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.84,1:27:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Science and consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.84,1:27:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of those things, when you, those conferences, calibrate in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.84,1:27:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll say it's like looking for ghosts with a Geiger counter.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.97,1:27:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the wrong tool, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.97,1:27:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the wrong tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.97,1:27:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect and science, logic, causality, the Newtonian paradigm is not how you arrive
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.97,1:27:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,at spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.97,1:27:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's got nothing to do with it, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.97,1:27:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what's the relationship between the two?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.35,1:27:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There ain't any.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.35,1:27:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.35,1:27:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the problem is a paradigm, paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.35,1:27:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a certain level of consciousness, you begin to see that certain things are more
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.35,1:27:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,important than facts.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.52,1:27:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is more important than whether it's logical, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.60,1:27:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, logic says this, but love says that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.60,1:27:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you recontextualize life from a new paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.64,1:27:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the value of everything is different.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.73,1:28:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, in the 400s, you look at pragmatic value.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.73,1:28:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 500s, you keep it because you love it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.02,1:28:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you throw that old thing away?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.02,1:28:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but because you love it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.02,1:28:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.02,1:28:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, on my desk, I have a cutesy little box some carpenter made.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.02,1:28:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have taken him weeks.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.02,1:28:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so incredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.02,1:28:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just enchanted with it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.02,1:28:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody comes in my office, I say, look at this, how it opens like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.02,1:28:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's not its worth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.02,1:28:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not its intellectual value at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.02,1:28:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can see what he put into that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.02,1:28:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what a piece of work.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.02,1:28:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll bring the box next time, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.02,1:28:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan bought it, came with an antique sewing machine,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.02,1:28:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which she's attached to, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.02,1:28:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, those modern computer models are much better,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.02,1:28:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but it isn't her little old antique sewing machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.02,1:28:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you see how the heart now begins to predominate.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.02,1:28:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,She loves her little antique sewing machine and sews on it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.15,1:28:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the computer model sits in the box, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.15,1:29:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's got directions.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.15,1:29:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They're sick, you know, in four languages.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.15,1:29:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts with Spanish, goes into Chinese, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.15,1:29:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, she's got it all done with this little machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.15,1:29:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So this adorable box.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.22,1:29:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, adorability.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.22,1:29:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I said adorable box.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.22,1:29:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a collector's item.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.22,1:29:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.22,1:29:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it appeals to some innate characteristic of humankind, humanity.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.22,1:29:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Quaintness, uniqueness, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.22,1:29:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It appeals to the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.52,1:29:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I never liked Frank Lloyd Wright.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.65,1:29:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't a heart in it at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.65,1:29:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Big slabs of coal, concrete, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.61,1:29:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a local bank we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.61,1:29:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is sleek and, you know, glass and plastic, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.61,1:29:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's highly efficient, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.61,1:29:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sure computers are happy there.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.61,1:29:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, there's no life around, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.61,1:30:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's completely non-life.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.61,1:30:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It would not nurture life, you know, so.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.64,1:30:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember the original, the same bank, National Bank has an office in Prescott.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.64,1:30:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's cute, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.64,1:30:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like 1892.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.64,1:30:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the spittoons, but there's big leather chairs and brass, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.64,1:30:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember like a bank looked in around 1910 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.64,1:30:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it looks like a place you'd put your money, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.64,1:30:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like solid citizens sitting there.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.64,1:30:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Cigars, spittoons, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.64,1:30:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so they opened a branch here and I went to this branch here and I thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.80,1:30:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to see a recapitulation, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.80,1:30:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I expected to walk into a sort of Victorian atmosphere and I was disappointed it was all cold modern.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.51,1:30:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.51,1:30:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So stripped of heart, stripped of heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.67,1:30:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so then we'll move on then.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.85,1:31:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So quaintness, cuteness, lovability is a whole different paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.89,1:31:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And this happens when your brain goes over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.89,1:31:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When consciousness level goes over 200, you shift from, this is your animal brain, below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.05,1:31:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how the relay is very fast through your emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.05,1:31:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Already you hate somebody and you haven't even had a chance to think about it because going through the cortex is slow.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.05,1:31:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it should be because this part is easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.11,1:31:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This part is eons old and the cortex is an add-on.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.27,1:31:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you have the animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.14,1:31:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this animal evolves to the point you put on the prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.14,1:31:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The only problem with the prefrontal cortex is it was plastered on the front of the old animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.14,1:31:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you're a better animal than you were before, smarter animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.14,1:32:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you see in the world, the conflict in the world is because the prefrontal cortex was plastered on the brains
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.97,1:32:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of people who calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.97,1:32:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore they are just an intelligent animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.13,1:32:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Out to get you, out to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.13,1:32:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can rationalize killing you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.13,1:32:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They can do it for God.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.13,1:32:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,God, I'm going to blow you all up because you're all infidels.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.13,1:32:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Boom, bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.13,1:32:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to heaven where there's all these, what do you call them, who's waiting for all these guys there?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.84,1:32:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,70 virgins, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.84,1:32:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I always tell the tale, what they don't tell you is when you get over there,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.89,1:32:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the 70 virgins are 90 years old, toothless, and they hate men.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.89,1:32:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He's picturing a go-go girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.97,1:32:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for you a long time, baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.35,1:32:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Waiting for you to come to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.15,1:32:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You got your 70 virgins all right, baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.76,1:33:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to take terms eating you alive, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.07,1:33:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Slowly, slowly, they eat the back of your neck so your head falls off, but slowly.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.92,1:33:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the 70 virgins waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.23,1:33:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.64,1:33:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200 then, you see the brain physiology changes amazingly.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.64,1:33:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You go right brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.47,1:33:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you celebrate quickly and then to the emotions and then it's stored in memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.47,1:33:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But the main thing here is at 200, you now develop an etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.47,1:33:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This sounded difficult to grasp when I first discovered it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.50,1:33:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, people do not have an etheric body or etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.50,1:33:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have an etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.68,1:33:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.27,1:33:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200 now, you develop an energy system, a spiritual energy system, and the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.32,1:33:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.32,1:34:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the etheric brain now in spiritual people sees and processes differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.32,1:34:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The physical brain does also.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.32,1:34:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But here, the fast track is through the etheric brain very fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.32,1:34:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get what the whole thing is about.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.32,1:34:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes through the cerebral cortex fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.32,1:34:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the right brain person, instead of responding and killing the guy and then deciding it probably wouldn't be a good idea later,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.81,1:34:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking for a spiritual solution to this guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.60,1:34:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.60,1:34:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already forgiven the guy before he even pulls the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.60,1:34:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.60,1:34:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you see what's coming up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.60,1:34:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus comes to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.60,1:34:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.60,1:34:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, Jesus' words come to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.60,1:34:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute your life is threatened.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.60,1:34:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life is threatened by an assassin.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.60,1:34:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.60,1:34:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.60,1:34:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already forgiving them for they don't know what they do.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.60,1:34:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see they're run by something.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.60,1:34:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs drugs.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.60,1:34:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs money.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.60,1:34:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what his problem is.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.60,1:34:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's God's problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.18,1:35:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see your etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.18,1:35:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're already heightened to a spiritual awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.18,1:35:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, therefore, we say it's linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.40,1:35:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're releasing adrenaline all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.64,1:35:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the fight or flight reaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.64,1:35:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stressful.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.64,1:35:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a struggle to the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.80,1:35:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a negative kinesiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.80,1:35:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So a calibration level below 200 triggers this.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.02,1:35:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And that triggers the arm goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.02,1:35:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So with kinesiology, it's not between true versus false.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.02,1:35:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there is no such thing as falsity.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.02,1:35:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only the absence of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.02,1:35:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.02,1:35:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like light.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.18,1:35:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Darkness is not the opposite of light.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.18,1:35:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the absence of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.18,1:35:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Absence of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.18,1:35:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So in nonduality, then, you bypass that positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.18,1:35:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see that good, goodness, et cetera, like light.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.68,1:36:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And truth is present to a variable degree.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.68,1:36:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When it reaches a low degree, we call that darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.68,1:36:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And when consciousness reaches a low degree, we call that evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.68,1:36:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're not opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.78,1:36:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that darkness is the absence of light.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.78,1:36:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.78,1:36:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you cannot have such a thing as non-light.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.78,1:36:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.92,1:36:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was equal, then you could have something called non-light.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.27,1:36:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd say, hey, show some non-light into this closet.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.27,1:36:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is comparable, then, to electricity running down a wire.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.27,1:36:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either on or it's not on.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.36,1:36:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no opposite of on-ness called off-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.60,1:36:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot send off-ness down electric wire.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.65,1:36:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.65,1:36:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one way you bypass duality, is to see that truth is a matter of gradations.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.43,1:36:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.43,1:37:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you get caught in the polarity of the opposites, which we'll get to later,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.43,1:37:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because we haven't even gotten to the title of today's lecture yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.43,1:37:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't want to be rigid, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.81,1:37:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, this is triggered by the release of kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.81,1:37:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Alignment with truth and divinity, devotion, all these things, and positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.93,1:37:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And you evolve to a certain point, and then there's the release of spiritual energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.06,1:37:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So the animal, from 200 down, people are run by, this is animal energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.06,1:37:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The left brain animal energy, and this is the physiology of left brain animal energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.22,1:37:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Not different than that of the tiger, the whale, or anybody there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.22,1:37:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the brain's physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.81,1:37:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What you had to do with spiritual energy, spiritual energy has a totally different quality.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.10,1:38:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual energy now, recontextualized, you have right brain dominance, it's non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.10,1:38:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're interested in is peace, you get the release of endorphins, positive emotions,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.43,1:38:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,increased immunity, better healing, you balance the acupuncture system,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.43,1:38:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get a positive kinesiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.43,1:38:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Positive kinesiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.77,1:38:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So like on-ness and off-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.06,1:38:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The kinesiologic response is the response, truth is either present, in which case the arm goes strong,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.15,1:38:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,or it's not present.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.15,1:38:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So the answer is yes or not yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.77,1:38:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not yes versus no.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.77,1:38:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise there would be such a thing in the world as no-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.77,1:38:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no no-ness anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.77,1:38:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't find non-ness or non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.77,1:38:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would you find the existence of non-existence, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.77,1:38:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.84,1:38:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that's enough of the didactic, academic.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.82,1:39:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Levels of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.31,1:39:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is important to know, because the level of happiness does not depend on acquisition.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.34,1:39:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of happiness, people's reported levels of happiness,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.34,1:39:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,are correlated almost exactly with their calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.34,1:39:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A very evolved person needs practically nothing at all to be happy in this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.50,1:39:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a cot, you've got a box, you've got an apple,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.50,1:39:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got a candle there,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.50,1:39:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've got a six-pack of Pepsi in the fridge.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.03,1:39:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And a pound of yak cheese.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.39,1:39:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave up yak cheese in that lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.39,1:39:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to eat yak cheese anymore, thank you God.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.39,1:39:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And sour camel milk.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.39,1:39:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you, I'm very happy to be American.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.39,1:39:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In the modern world, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.81,1:39:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.94,1:39:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.94,1:40:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, the interesting thing here is the minute you jump over 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.19,1:40:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the rate of happiness more than doubles.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.19,1:40:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you jump down here, these people think they're happy,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.27,1:40:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's because they're delusional.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.27,1:40:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't know any better.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.27,1:40:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Breathing in and out makes them happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.27,1:40:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, instantly, the minute you're over 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.84,1:40:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of being happy increases and eventually reaches,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.84,1:40:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which is 100%.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.84,1:40:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you have no needs from the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.84,1:40:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you have to prove about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.84,1:40:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you have to gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.84,1:40:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is complete and total within itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.88,1:40:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean that you can't envision, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.88,1:40:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,being a help to society or a better world,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.88,1:40:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or having cutesy sewing boxes.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.60,1:40:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But those are additions, those are elaborations.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.60,1:40:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be depressed this morning because we didn't get a cutesy little,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.60,1:41:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,wooden box to put the sewing parts in, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.60,1:41:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be depressed about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.60,1:41:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right, so what you need from the world is very minimal.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.60,1:41:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What you need from the world is very minimal.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.60,1:41:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a value to asceticism.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.60,1:41:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Asceticism to become aware of your avarice for the pleasures of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.60,1:41:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then discover that without any of them, practically,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.60,1:41:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be happy as a clam.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.60,1:41:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can live without money.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.60,1:41:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You can live without anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.35,1:41:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I walked out the door with nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.35,1:41:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing at all, not even food.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.89,1:41:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And sure enough, around noontime, somebody said,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.05,1:41:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,hey, you going for lunch?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.05,1:41:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, no, I haven't got any money.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.05,1:41:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I'll take you for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.05,1:41:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Lunch appeared itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.05,1:41:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinner appeared itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.05,1:41:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The next morning, somebody came over with rolls or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.23,1:41:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He bought too many.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.23,1:41:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, even food just appeared out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.23,1:41:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.23,1:42:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, correlation of that with greater happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.00,1:42:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.64,1:42:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.64,1:42:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We think we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.64,1:42:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We have hopes to move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.64,1:42:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Our intention is to move on and collapse the wave function.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.38,1:42:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll collapse the wave function just in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.38,1:42:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God for our intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.38,1:42:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Betty, and your intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.47,1:42:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we collapsed the wave function.
